'''''Andromache Mourning Hector''''' is a 1783 oil painting by [[Jacques-Louis David]]. The painting depicts an image from [[Homer]]'s ''[[Iliad]]'', showing [[Andromache]], comforted by her son, [[Astyanax]], mourning over her husband [[Hector]], who has been killed by [[Achilles]].<ref>{{cite web| publisher=Boston College| title=Jacques-Louis David:Andromache Mourning HectorJacques-Louis David: Andromache Mourning Hector| accessdate=2014-07-11| url=http://www.bc.edu/bc_org/avp/cas/his/CoreArt/art/neocl_dav_andro.html}}</ref> This painting, presented on 23 August 1783, brought David election to the [[Académie royale de peinture et de sculpture|Académie Royale]] in 1784.<ref>{{cite web| publisher=bio.| title=Jacques-Louis David Biography| accessdate=2014-07-11| url=http://www.biography.com/people/jacques-louis-david-9267043?page=2}}</ref>
